sca.title: Regular Expression Denial of Service - mime
sca.description: Affected versions of `mime` are vulnerable to regular expression denial of service when a mime lookup is performed on untrusted user input.

sca.title: Memory Exposure - bl
sca.description:
Versions of `bl` before 0.9.5 and 1.0.1 are vulnerable to memory exposure.

`bl.append(number)` in the affected `bl` versions passes a number to Buffer constructor, appending a chunk of uninitialized memory

sca.title: Remote Memory Exposure - bl
sca.description: A buffer over-read vulnerability exists in bl <4.0.3, <3.0.1 <2.2.1 and <1.2.3 which could allow an attacker to supply user input (even typed) that if it ends up in consume() argument and can become negative, the BufferList state can be corrupted, tricking it into exposing uninitialized memory via regular .slice() calls.
